Sentencas: The sheet resistance of patterned electrodes was modeled and corrected using a finite volume technique.
Titulo: Modeling of patterned mixed-conducting electrodes and the importance of sheet resistance at small feature sizes

Sentencas: Results show that the sheet resistance of patterned electrodes may dramatically reduce the utilization or the performance of the electrodes when the feature size (e.g., thickness or width) is sufficiently small.
Titulo: Modeling of patterned mixed-conducting electrodes and the importance of sheet resistance at small feature sizes

Sentencas: Further, the utilization of a patterned electrode with a given geometry can be estimated, which may be used for correcting the sheet resistance effect on electrode performance.
Titulo: Modeling of patterned mixed-conducting electrodes and the importance of sheet resistance at small feature sizes

Sentencas: These results are important not only to fundamental study of electrode reaction mechanisms and kinetics but also to better design of porous mixed-conducting electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Modeling of patterned mixed-conducting electrodes and the importance of sheet resistance at small feature sizes
